{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, traditional fact-checking methods involving human efforts to manually verify the accuracy of claims cannot scale with the sheer volume and speed of information being shared online.",
    "Automatic misinformation detection could potentially overcome the problem of scale.",
    "But when they work, these methods rely on extensive language features such as writing style, lexicon, and emotion [9].",
    "Therefore they need to be constantly retrained to reflect new knowledge and evolving tactics employed by purveyors of false information.",
    "These challenges are exacerbated by the rise of content created by generative AI."
  ]
}